Citation.sTitle: Excess Molar Volume along with Viscosity and Refractive Index for Binary Systems of Tricyclo[5.2.1.0(2.6)]decane with Five Cycloalkanes
Citation.sAbstract: Densities, viscosities, and refractive indices have been measured for the binary system of tricyclo[5.2.1.02.6]decane with cyclohexane, methylcyclohexane, ethylcyclohexane, butylcyclohexane, or 1,2,4-trimethylcyclohexane at temperatures T = (293.15 to 318.15 K) and pressure p = 0.1 MPa. The excess molar volumes (VmE), the viscosity deviations (??), and the refractive index deviations (?nD) are then calculated. The changes of VmE and ?? with the composition are fitted to the Redlich Kister equation. The values of density, viscosity, and refractive index increase continuously with the increase of mole fraction of tricyclo[5.2.1.02.6]decane and decrease with the rise of temperature. The VmE and ?? are all negative over the whole composition range for these five binary systems. The changes of VmE and ?? are discussed from the points of view of molecular interactions in the binary systems.
